===Etymology===
1619; alteration of earlier {{m|en|wolvering}} (1574), diminutive of {{m|en|wolver}} ‘ravenous or savage animal; person who behaves like a wolf’ (1593),<ref>Robert K. Barnhart, ed., ''Chambers Dictionary of Etymology'' (Edinburgh: Chambers, 2008), 1242.</ref> ultimately from {{m|en|wolf}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈwʊlvəˌriːn/|/ˈwɒlvəˌriːn/|lang=en}}, US also: /ˌwʊlvəˈriːn/

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A solitary, fierce [[mammal]] of the [[Mustelidae]] family, ''[[Gulo gulo]]''.
#* '''1920''', [[w:Peter B. Kyne|Peter B. Kyne]], ''The Understanding Heart'', Chapter IV
